    "headline": "Alphabet's Wing to start drone delivery in San Francisco Bay Area",
    "summary": "Alphabet-owned Wing plans to begin delivering packages by drone to homes in California's San Francisco ‌Bay Area in the coming months, it said on ‌Monday, extending its rollout to one of its earliest testing grounds.  Wing is seeking ​to scale what it says is a solution to the hurdles facing last-mile delivery of small household items and meals by using lightweight, automated drones designed to fly directly to homes in ‌dense residential areas.  The expansion ⁠marks a return to the roots for the company, which was founded in the Bay Area ⁠in 2012 as part of Alphabet's X.",
